HERE, JACK,

11:21.667 --> 11:22.291
IS THAT I STILL
HAVE MY DIGNITY.

11:22.291 --> 11:25.125
MMPH.

11:27.750 --> 11:29.834
SO...

11:29.834 --> 11:30.959
WHAT ARE YOU
DOIN' TONIGHT?

11:30.959 --> 11:32.834
ACTUALLY, I KNOW THIS BAR
THAT DOES NOT CARD.

11:32.834 --> 11:35.917
SOLD.
YEAH, PACE,
I GOTTA TELL YA--

11:35.917 --> 11:37.750
TELL ME ON THE WAY.

11:37.750 --> 11:38.708
OK.

11:38.708 --> 11:39.959
DO YOU REALIZE WHERE
WE ARE RIGHT NOW?

11:39.959 --> 11:41.500
WE ARE BACKSTAGE
AT A ROCK CONCERT.

11:41.500 --> 11:43.417
HOW COOL IS THAT?

11:43.417 --> 11:44.708
ACTUALLY,
WE'RE LOST BACKSTAGE

11:44.708 --> 11:45.625
AT A ROCK CONCERT,

11:45.625 --> 11:46.667
WHICH IS SIGNIFICANTLY
LESS COOL.

11:46.667 --> 11:49.750
I THOUGHT THAT
THE GUY SAID 3 LEFTS.

11:49.750 --> 11:52.208
3 LEFTS WOULD BE
A CIRCLE, AUDREY.

11:52.208 --> 11:53.875
NO. 4 LEFTS IS A CIRCLE.
ANYWAY, IT DOESN'T MATTER.

11:53.875 --> 11:56.750
WE'RE BACKSTAGE
AT A ROCK CONCERT.

11:56.750 --> 11:58.542
LET'S GO THIS WAY.

11:58.542 --> 11:59.708
ALL RIGHT,
BEFORE WE GET THERE,

11:59.708 --> 12:01.083
YOU HAVE TO PROMISE
TO LET ME HAVE THE CUTE ONE.

12:01.083 --> 12:02.375
YOU SAID THAT
THEY WERE ALL CUTE.

12:02.375 --> 12:04.125
WELL, YEAH, ONSTAGE.

12:04.125 --> 12:05.875
EVERYBODY'S CUTE
ONSTAGE, YOU KNOW?

12:05.875 --> 12:06.625
I MEAN, LIKE,
THE WHOLE BUZZ,

12:06.625 --> 12:09.417
THE MUSIC, INSTRUMENTS.

12:09.417 --> 12:10.667
THEIR MUSIC WAS AWFUL.

12:10.667 --> 12:12.041
IT WAS PUERILE
AND--AND GIMMICKY.

12:12.041 --> 12:14.583
OK, JUST LET ME HAVE
THE LEAD SINGER, ALL RIGHT?

12:14.583 --> 12:17.041
OK, FINE,
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

12:17.041 --> 12:18.917
UH, JUST TO SET
THE RECORD STRAIGHT,

12:18.917 --> 12:21.125
YOU MAY BE HERE
ON SOME MISGUIDED,

12:21.125 --> 12:22.041
HORMONALLY CHARGED
ATTEMPT

12:22.041 --> 12:24.166
TO GET THE PACEY
OUT OF YOUR SYSTEM--

12:24.166 --> 12:24.792
WHICH YOU PROMISED
NOT TO COMMENT ON.

12:24.792 --> 12:26.458
AND I'M NOT GOING TO--

12:26.458 --> 12:27.542
BUT I,
ON THE OTHER HAND,

12:27.542 --> 12:29.417
AM HERE OUT OF PURELY
PROFESSIONAL REASONS.

12:29.417 --> 12:31.500
I'M GOING
TO MEET THIS BAND.

12:31.500 --> 12:33.250
I'M GOING TO TAKE THEM BACK
TO THE RADIO STATION,

12:33.250 --> 12:34.750
INTERVIEW THEM, AND
THEN I GO HOME TO DAWSON.

12:34.750 --> 12:37.000
WHO'S OUT RIGHT NOW
WITH JOEY.

12:38.166 --> 12:39.667
WHICH DOESN'T
BOTHER ME A BIT.

12:39.667 --> 12:42.417
BECAUSE I,
UNLIKE YOU,

12:42.417 --> 12:44.583
AM TOTALLY CAPABLE
OF HAVING A MATURE,

12:44.583 --> 12:47.208
COMMITTED, TRUSTING,
ADULT RELATIONSHIP,

12:47.208 --> 12:48.375
AND I WOULD REALLY
APPRECIATE IT

12:48.375 --> 12:51.458
IF YOU COULD JUST SHOW
A MODICUM OF PROFES--

12:53.125 --> 12:54.625
HEY.
HI.

12:54.625 --> 12:57.250
HEY, WYNN, DID WE ORDER
2 BEAUTIFUL BLONDES?

12:58.917 --> 13:01.708
UH, YES, YES,
WE DID. WYNN.

13:01.708 --> 13:02.792
HI.
Wynn: HI.

13:02.792 --> 13:04.834
I'M JEN FROM WBCW.

13:04.834 --> 13:05.583
THIS IS
MY FRIEND AUDREY.

13:05.583 --> 13:07.792
UM, YOU'RE STEPHEN?

13:07.792 --> 13:10.542
STEVE, JUST--JUST
CALL ME STEVE.

13:10.542 --> 13:12.041
Wynn: SO WHAT'D
YOU THINK?

13:13.542 --> 13:16.041
IT WAS A GREAT SET.

13:16.041 --> 13:16.500
YOU DID--IT WAS...

13:16.500 --> 13:17.375
REALLY GOOD.

13:17.375 --> 13:19.375
YEAH.
MAN.

13:20.375 --> 13:21.333
WE'LL GO GET OUR COATS.

13:21.333 --> 13:22.500
OK.

13:22.500 --> 13:24.583
CHANGED MY MIND.

13:24.583 --> 13:26.500
WANT THE ONE
WITH THE BEARD.

13:27.625 --> 13:29.959
SO I TAKE IT
YOU'RE STARTING
TO LIKE IT HERE?

13:29.959 --> 13:31.000
YEAH. I AM.

13:31.000 --> 13:33.250
AT FIRST, I DIDN'T
THINK I'D FIT IN, BUT--

13:33.250 --> 13:35.125
AND NOW YOU'RE
JUST AS PRETENTIOUS
AS THE REST OF THEM.

13:35.125 --> 13:37.125
GODARD IS NOT PRETENTIOUS.
HE'S VERY FUNNY.

13:37.125 --> 13:38.208
HOW COULD YOU
NOT LOVE A MOVIE

13:38.208 --> 13:39.000
WHERE THE GUY'S FAKE NAME
ON THE PASSPORT

13:39.000 --> 13:39.917
IS LÁSZLÓ KOVÁCS?

13:39.917 --> 13:42.125
WELL, IT HELPS
IF YOU HAVE NO IDEA

13:42.125 --> 13:43.250
WHO THAT IS.

13:43.250 --> 13:45.125
HE'S AN INCREDIBLY
FAMOUS CINEMATOGRAPHER.

13:45.125 --> 13:46.959
YOU USED
TO KNOW THIS STUFF.

13:46.959 --> 13:49.667
WRONG. I ONLY PRETENDED
TO KNOW STUFF LIKE THIS

13:49.667 --> 13:50.875
SO THAT YOU WOULD BE
IMPRESSED WITH ME.

13:50.875 --> 13:52.667
[LAUGHS] YOU ARE
WAY MORE OF A GIRL

13:52.667 --> 13:54.875
THAN I EVER IMAGINED.

13:54.875 --> 13:56.708
YEAH, WELL,
YOU'RE WAY MORE
INTO FRENCH CINEMA.

13:56.708 --> 13:57.917
ISN'T THAT
YOUR, UH, TEACHER?

13:57.917 --> 13:59.166
WHAT?

13:59.166 --> 14:00.792
THE--THE DARK-HAIRED GUY.
I CAN'T REMEMBER HIS NAME--

14:00.792 --> 14:01.834
YOUR PROFESSOR.

14:01.834 --> 14:02.750
HELLO.

14:02.750 --> 14:06.625
YOU LOOK GREAT.
MM-MM-MM-MMPH.

14:06.625 --> 14:08.375
YEAH, I GUESS IT IS.

14:10.417 --> 14:12.750
SHOULD WE GO SAY HELLO?

14:14.625 --> 14:15.792
LET'S NOT.

14:15.792 --> 14:23.333
AH, GREAT.
THAT'S GREAT.

14:23.333 --> 14:25.834
OK.

14:32.333 --> 14:35.208
Pacey: SO I WONDER WHAT
THEY'RE DOING RIGHT NOW?

14:35.208 --> 14:36.542
ARE YOU THINKIN'
ABOUT CHASIN'?

14:36.542 --> 14:38.708
ME? NAH.

14:38.708 --> 14:40.166
WHY? YOU THINK I SHOULD?

14:40.166 --> 14:41.417
CHASE HER?

14:41.417 --> 14:43.208
WELL, WHEN YOU WEIGH
A LITTLE PERSONAL PRIDE

14:43.208 --> 14:45.458
AGAINST THE OPPORTUNITY
FOR GREAT SEX, IT'S--

14:45.458 --> 14:46.000
SEX WINS.

14:46.000 --> 14:47.708
YES, EVERY TIME,

14:47.708 --> 14:49.208
AND WOMEN DO
LIKE TO BE CHASED.

14:49.208 --> 14:51.750
RIGHT UP TO THE POINT
WHERE THEY FILE FOR
THAT RESTRAINING ORDER.

14:51.750 --> 14:53.542
RIGHT. YOU GOT
A GOOD POINT THERE.

14:53.542 --> 14:55.125
I GENERALLY DO. CHEERS.

14:55.125 --> 14:56.166
CHEERS.
[GLASSES CLINK]

14:56.166 --> 14:57.375
THOUGH, I'M
NOT REALLY SURE

14:57.375 --> 14:58.458
WE SHOULD BE DOING THIS.

14:58.458 --> 15:00.291
WHAT, DRINKIN'?

15:00.291 --> 15:01.875
I TOLD YA. THEY DON'T
CARD AT THIS PLACE.

15:01.875 --> 15:03.625
NO. I'M TALKIN' ABOUT
YOUR RECENT TRACK RECORD.

15:03.625 --> 15:04.792
YOU SEE, I'D HATE TO SPEND
THE NIGHT IN JAIL

15:04.792 --> 15:06.834
AFTER YOU RUN INTO A COUPLE
OF YOUR FRAT BROTHERS

15:06.834 --> 15:08.625
AND DO A LITTLE DANCE
ON THEIR SKULLS.

15:08.625 --> 15:10.000
DRINK UP, WILL YOU?

15:10.000 --> 15:11.000
IT'S NOT GONNA
HAPPEN HERE.

15:11.000 --> 15:11.667
THIS ISN'T
THE KIND OF PLACE.

15:11.667 --> 15:13.125
I LIKE THIS PLACE, MAN.

15:13.125 --> 15:16.125
THEY GOT CHEAP BEER,
LATE-NIGHT APPETIZER MENU.

15:18.708 --> 15:19.583
THE ONLY PROBLEM IS

15:19.583 --> 15:21.917
THERE'S NOT
A LOT OF WOMEN HERE.

15:29.542 --> 15:31.375
JACK, THIS WOULDN'T
HAPPEN TO BE A--

15:31.375 --> 15:32.667
MM-HMM. PRETTY MUCH.

15:32.667 --> 15:35.959
THAT MUCH, HUH?

15:35.959 --> 15:37.917
THAT MUCH.
WELL, IT'S FUNNY.

15:37.917 --> 15:38.959
IT REALLY DOESN'T SEEM
LIKE IT'S ALL THAT...

15:38.959 --> 15:40.417
GAY?

15:40.417 --> 15:41.250
I KNOW. THAT'S
WHY I LIKE IT.

15:41.250 --> 15:43.333
LISTEN, I GOTTA
HIT THE HEAD.

15:43.333 --> 15:44.834
OHH.

15:44.834 --> 15:46.375
AHEM.

15:46.375 --> 15:47.750
HEY, YOU'RE NOT, LIKE,
YOU KNOW...

15:47.750 --> 15:49.542
WEIRDED OUT BY ALL THIS.

15:49.542 --> 15:51.000
ME? NAH.

15:51.000 --> 15:52.250
'CAUSE I PROBABLY
SHOULD HAVE MENTIONED,
YOU KNOW--

15:52.250 --> 15:54.750
LOOK, JACK, LIKE,
I NEVER BEEN
IN A GAY BAR BEFORE.

15:54.750 --> 15:56.166
YEAH.

15:56.166 --> 15:57.542
YOU GUYS ARE GREAT.

16:00.583 --> 16:02.166
[STUTTERS]

16:02.166 --> 16:03.250
[MUSIC PLAYING]
Jen: YOU KNOW, IF YOU
WANNA JUST TELL ME

16:03.250 --> 16:04.250
WHAT IT IS THAT
YOU'RE LOOKING FOR,

16:04.250 --> 16:06.458
I COULD PROBABLY
HELP YOU FIND IT.

16:06.458 --> 16:09.834
LET'S SEE. AH, SUCCESS.

16:09.834 --> 16:10.792
DONOVAN.

16:10.792 --> 16:12.875
THE SIXTIES DONOVAN?

16:12.875 --> 16:15.959
DONOVAN IS LONG OVERDUE
FOR A MAJOR REVIVAL.

16:15.959 --> 16:17.458
[LAUGHS] NOT ON
MY RADIO SHOW HE'S NOT.

16:17.458 --> 16:19.333
SOUNDS LIKE SOMEONE
DOESN'T LIKE LOSING CONTROL.

16:19.333 --> 16:21.583
OK, WHY DON'T WE JUST
KEEP THE PERSONAL STUFF
OUT OF THIS,

16:21.583 --> 16:23.083
AND WE CAN
STICK TO MUSIC.

16:24.166 --> 16:26.375
DO YOU HAVE A BOYFRIEND?

16:26.375 --> 16:29.375
IT'S NONE OF
YOUR BUSINESS.

16:29.375 --> 16:31.083
[CLICKS TONGUE]

16:32.875 --> 16:35.959
[MUSIC ENDS]
IT'S OVER.

16:35.959 --> 16:36.625
UH, WHE--WHEN? WHAT?

16:36.625 --> 16:37.792
THE SONG...

16:37.792 --> 16:39.125
ON THE RADIO. IT'S OVER.

16:40.959 --> 16:42.792
OH!
YEAH.

16:46.250 --> 16:48.834
SO AFTER THIS,
THEN WHAT?

16:48.834 --> 16:51.625
NEW YORK, PHILLY, D.C.,

16:51.625 --> 16:55.125
AND HEAD BACK DOWN SOUTH--
THE CAROLINAS--

16:55.125 --> 16:57.708
WHERE YOU'LL FIND
EXCELLENT BARBECUE

16:57.708 --> 16:59.625
AND ONE OF THE GREATEST
ROCK AND ROLL VENUES EVER.

16:59.625 --> 17:01.458
REALLY?

17:01.458 --> 17:02.625
MM-HMM.

17:02.625 --> 17:03.667
WHAT'S SO GREAT
ABOUT IT?

17:03.667 --> 17:05.040
LAUNDROMAT ON ONE SIDE,

17:05.040 --> 17:06.165
USED RECORD STORE
ON THE OTHER.

17:06.165 --> 17:09.375
WHAT, YOU CAN'T ROCK
WITHOUT CLEAN SOCKS?

17:09.375 --> 17:10.666
[LAUGHS] WELL, I CAN,

17:10.666 --> 17:11.458
BUT I PREFER NOT TO.

17:11.458 --> 17:12.541
RIGHT.

17:12.541 --> 17:15.416
AND THEN?

17:15.416 --> 17:18.666
HOME. CHARLOTTESVILLE,
VIRGINIA.

17:18.666 --> 17:19.458
YEAH, THAT'S WHERE
MY GIRLFRIEND LIVES.

17:19.458 --> 17:21.250
MM-HMM.

17:25.083 --> 17:27.208
KIM.

17:27.208 --> 17:30.250
SHE'S GETTING HER Ph.D.
IN ANTHROPOLOGY.

17:30.250 --> 17:31.583
SHE'S PRETTY.

17:31.583 --> 17:35.834
YEAH, AND THAT'S
OUR VICIOUS DOG BOWIE.

17:35.834 --> 17:38.708
OH, WELL, IT'S NICE.

17:38.708 --> 17:40.875
YEAH, IT IS.

17:40.875 --> 17:43.375
BORING, THOUGH.

17:43.375 --> 17:45.417
THAT'S WHAT
YOU'RE THINKING, RIGHT?

17:45.417 --> 17:47.375
WELL...

17:47.375 --> 17:49.250
NOW THAT YOU MENTION IT.

17:49.250 --> 17:50.333
I DON'T KNOW.

17:50.333 --> 17:52.375
IT DOESN'T SEEM VERY
ROCK AND ROLL, DOES IT?

17:52.375 --> 17:54.041
WHAT, MONOGAMY?

17:54.041 --> 17:56.500
YEAH. COME ON.

17:56.500 --> 17:57.667
DON'T YOU EVER
GET THE URGE

17:57.667 --> 17:58.750
TO DO SOMETHING BAD?

17:58.750 --> 18:02.166
YEAH, BUT I DON'T.

18:02.166 --> 18:04.208
I MEAN, I LOVE
MY GIRLFRIEND.

18:04.208 --> 18:06.000
AND IT'S REALLY JUST
THAT SIMPLE FOR YOU?

18:06.000 --> 18:08.542
YEAH. WHY WOULDN'T IT BE?

18:08.542 --> 18:12.083
I DON'T KNOW.
I GUESS I JUST--

18:12.083 --> 18:14.417
I THINK OF RELATIONSHIPS

18:14.417 --> 18:16.375
AS BEING MORE
COMPLICATED THAN THAT.

18:16.375 --> 18:17.458
THEY ARE.

18:17.458 --> 18:18.208
BAD RELATIONSHIPS.

18:22.083 --> 18:23.125
[PACEY SIGHS]

18:23.125 --> 18:24.083
THAT'S NOT BREAD.
IT'S SAWDUST.

18:24.083 --> 18:25.125
I MEAN,
AT CIVILIZATION

18:25.125 --> 18:27.208
WE BAKE THE STUFF
OURSELF, OK?

18:27.208 --> 18:28.083
PACEY.

18:28.083 --> 18:29.959
HEY, JACK. GOOD
TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

18:29.959 --> 18:31.750
LET ME INTRODUCE
YOU. JEFF, JEFF,
JACK, JACK, JEFF.

18:31.750 --> 18:32.917
HEY, JEFF.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

18:32.917 --> 18:34.667
UH, TALK TO YOU
FOR A SEC.

18:34.667 --> 18:36.792
SURE THING.
EXCUSE ME
FOR A SECOND.

18:36.792 --> 18:38.417
CAN YOU BELIEVE
WHAT A SMALL WORLD
IT IS?

18:38.417 --> 18:39.458
THAT GUY'S
A FOOD CRITIC

18:39.458 --> 18:41.250
FOR A VERY BIG
MAGAZINE IN TOWN,

18:41.250 --> 18:43.583
AND HE SAID HE'D
PRETTY MUCH GIVEN UP
ON CIVILIZATION,

18:43.583 --> 18:45.750
RIGHT? I BELIEVE
PASSÉ WAS HIS WORD,

18:45.750 --> 18:46.625
BUT I'M CHANGIN'
ALL THAT.

18:46.625 --> 18:47.875
HMM.

18:47.875 --> 18:49.542
SO HOW LONG YOU BEEN
TALKIN' TO THAT GUY?

18:49.542 --> 18:50.875
I DON'T KNOW.
COUPLE MINUTES.
WHO CARES?

18:50.875 --> 18:51.667
WHAT'S IMPORTANT

18:51.667 --> 18:53.125
IS THAT HE IS
THIS FAR AWAY

18:53.125 --> 18:54.166
FROM GIVING US
A WRITE-UP.

18:54.166 --> 18:56.083
HMM. WHAT'S HE WANT
IN RETURN?

18:56.083 --> 18:56.333
EH-EH.

18:59.834 --> 19:01.959
WAIT. YOU DON'T
THINK THAT HE THINKS
THAT I'M--

19:01.959 --> 19:03.166
MM-HMM. YEAH, YEAH.

19:03.166 --> 19:04.375
UNLESS SOME TIME
IN THE PAST FEW MINUTES

19:04.375 --> 19:06.625
YOU'VE JUST HAPPENED
TO MENTION THE FACT THAT,

19:06.625 --> 19:09.291
UH, GEE, I DON'T KNOW,
YOU'RE NOT GAY.

19:09.291 --> 19:12.291
JACK, LOOK AT ME, OK?
REALLY LOOK AT ME.

19:12.291 --> 19:14.458
I'M A SCHLUB, OK?
I'M NOT GAY FRIENDLY.

19:14.458 --> 19:15.333
I WOULD BE
AN INSULT TO GAYDOM.

19:15.333 --> 19:16.417
OK, YOU MIGHT HAVE
A POINT THERE,

19:16.417 --> 19:19.333
BUT THE GUY WAS HANGIN'
ON YOUR EVERY WORD.

19:19.333 --> 19:20.667
SURE HE WAS. SO?

19:20.667 --> 19:22.500
SO YOU'RE NOT
THAT INTERESTING.

19:22.500 --> 19:23.041
I'M NOT?

19:23.041 --> 19:25.625
NO. HE--LOOK...

19:25.625 --> 19:26.792
NOBODY LISTENS
THAT HARD, OK,

19:26.792 --> 19:29.208
UNLESS THEY'RE JUST
TRYIN' TO, YOU KNOW--

19:29.208 --> 19:29.417
OH.

19:32.792 --> 19:33.834
INTERESTING.

19:33.834 --> 19:35.208
WHAT?

19:35.208 --> 19:36.291
WELL...

19:36.291 --> 19:39.166
I THINK FOR THE FIRST
TIME IN MY LIFE,

19:39.166 --> 19:39.917
I UNDERSTAND
WHAT IT MUST BE LIKE

19:39.917 --> 19:42.333
TO BE A WOMAN,

19:42.333 --> 19:44.166
A REALLY HOT WOMAN.

19:44.166 --> 19:46.708
OH. UH...

19:46.708 --> 19:49.208
NOT THAT HOT.

19:49.208 --> 19:50.542
I'M NOT?

19:50.542 --> 19:51.583
NOT REALLY.

19:51.583 --> 19:53.667
I MEAN--LOOK, COULD WE--

19:53.667 --> 19:54.708
WHAT ARE WE GONNA
DO HERE, ALL RIGHT?

19:54.708 --> 19:56.125
YOU WANNA GO OVER
AND TELL HIM OR SHOULD I?

19:56.125 --> 19:57.667
WHAT? WE CAN'T
TELL HIM NOW.

19:57.667 --> 19:59.667
HE'S GONNA THINK
THAT I PURPOSEFULLY
DECEIVED HIM.

19:59.667 --> 20:01.000
ALL RIGHT,
SO I'LL GO OVER,

20:01.000 --> 20:01.834
AND I WILL JUST
EXPLAIN TO HIM

20:01.834 --> 20:03.125
WHAT AN IDIOT YOU ARE.

20:03.125 --> 20:05.875
OR WE COULD JUST GLOSS
OVER THAT IDIOT THING

20:05.875 --> 20:06.834
FOR THE NEXT
LITTLE WHILE,

20:06.834 --> 20:09.166
UNTIL HE AGREES
TO DO THE STORY,

20:09.166 --> 20:10.375
BECAUSE HE IS
A MAJOR CRITIC,

20:10.375 --> 20:12.750
AND THIS WOULD MEAN
A TON OF BUSINESS

20:12.750 --> 20:13.875
FOR MY RESTAURANT.

20:13.875 --> 20:16.250
I KNOW. I KNOW,
BUT WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO

20:16.250 --> 20:17.750
WHEN HE ASKS YOU
FOR YOUR NUMBER, HUH?

20:18.625 --> 20:20.125
I WILL LOOK HIM
RIGHT IN THE EYE

20:20.125 --> 20:22.917
AND GIVE HIM
YOUR PHONE NUMBER.

20:22.917 --> 20:24.375
YOU WOULDN'T--

20:24.375 --> 20:26.166
NO. COME ON.
WE'RE TELLIN' THE TRUTH.

20:26.166 --> 20:28.667
[GROANS]

20:28.667 --> 20:30.125
[MUSIC ENDS]

20:30.125 --> 20:32.959
[SIGHS] ALL RIGHT,
UH, SO WE ARE BACK,

20:32.959 --> 20:36.542
UH, FOLKS, WITH VENEER
IN TOWN 2 NIGHTS,

20:36.542 --> 20:37.875
OPENING
FOR NORTH AMERICA,

20:37.875 --> 20:40.792
ON THEIR APTLY TITLED
NORTH AMERICAN TOUR.

20:40.792 --> 20:42.250
YOU KNOW, I NEVER
REALLY GOT THAT.

20:42.250 --> 20:44.834
WE NEVER WENT
TO CANADA, NOT ONCE.

20:44.834 --> 20:45.834
OR MEXICO.

20:45.834 --> 20:47.083
CHICAGO TWICE.

20:47.083 --> 20:48.708
UH, LISTEN,
SO OPENING SUCKS, RIGHT?

20:48.708 --> 20:52.708
NO, NOT WHEN YOU'RE
OPENING FOR A TOTALLY
ROCKIN' BAND

20:52.708 --> 20:53.792
LIKE NORTH AMERICA.

20:53.792 --> 20:57.166
YEAH, BUT SERIOUSLY, UH,
THERE'S A WHOLE CROWD

20:57.166 --> 21:00.542
THAT'S NOT THERE TO SEE YOU.

21:00.542 --> 21:03.417
THEY'RE IMPATIENT. THEY
JUST WANNA GET IT OVER WITH.

21:03.417 --> 21:06.250
TRUE, BUT, YOU KNOW,
SOMETIMES YOU WIN THEM OVER,

21:06.250 --> 21:07.792
AND THEN THE VICTORY'S
EVEN SWEETER.

21:07.792 --> 21:09.333
HOW SO?

21:09.333 --> 21:12.917
WELL, MORE THAN LIKELY
THEY PREJUDGED YOU.

21:12.917 --> 21:14.583
THEY'VE TAKEN
ONE LOOK AT YOU,

21:14.583 --> 21:17.291
AND THEY'VE SAID,
"NO, NOT FOR ME."

21:17.291 --> 21:20.083
AND THEN WE PROCEED
TO ROCK.

21:21.792 --> 21:24.625
WE DON'T ASK FOR A LOT.

21:29.417 --> 21:31.250
HERE IS GOOD.

21:32.667 --> 21:35.208
YEAH.

21:37.834 --> 21:39.500
[SIGHS]

21:46.583 --> 21:49.750
YOU SURE YOU DON'T WANNA
JUST GO OVER AND SAY HI?

21:49.750 --> 21:51.208
GOD, NO. HOW EMBARRASSING
WOULD THAT BE?

21:51.208 --> 21:53.708
I MEAN, HE'S OBVIOUSLY
ON A DATE OR SOMETHING.

21:53.708 --> 21:55.000
YEAH, BUT IF HE SEES YOU,

21:55.000 --> 21:56.875
ISN'T HE GONNA WONDER WHY
YOU DIDN'T SAY SOMETHING?

21:56.875 --> 21:58.375
WHAT'S THE MOVIE
ABOUT ANYWAY?

21:58.375 --> 22:00.667
[LAUGHS] SHE SAYS,
CHANGING THE SUBJECT.

22:00.667 --> 22:01.917
WELL?

22:01.917 --> 22:03.875
UH, HUMPHREY BOGART
IS A STRUGGLING
SCREENWRITER,

22:03.875 --> 22:07.834
UH, ACCUSED OF MURDER.
IT'S--IT'S NOIR
EXCEPT IT'S NOT,

22:07.834 --> 22:10.375
SO THE WHOLE THING
IS SORT OF FAMOUSLY
AMBIGUOUS.

22:10.375 --> 22:11.959
SO YOU PRETTY MUCH
HAVE TO BE A FILM GEEK

22:11.959 --> 22:13.792
TO WANNA SEE IT.

22:13.792 --> 22:15.792
OR YOU HAVE TO BE
A REALLY GOOD FRIEND
OF THE FILM GEEK.

22:17.333 --> 22:19.375
RIGHT. LIKE US. THEY COULD
JUST BE FRIENDS.

22:19.375 --> 22:22.417
YOUR TEACHER AND
THE GIRL HE'S KISSING?

22:28.041 --> 22:30.250
JOEY?

22:30.250 --> 22:33.208
DO YOU HAVE
A CRUSH ON YOUR
ENGLISH PROFESSOR?

22:33.208 --> 22:34.625
WHAT?

22:34.959 --> 22:37.208
NO.

22:38.542 --> 22:40.500
IT'S--IT'S WEIRD.

22:40.500 --> 22:42.375
IT'S NOT THAT WEIRD.
TEACHERS DO HAVE
PERSONAL LIVES.

22:42.375 --> 22:43.625
THEY HAVE BEEN KNOWN
TO KISS PEOPLE

22:43.625 --> 22:44.959
FROM TIME TO TIME.

22:44.959 --> 22:46.708
YEAH, LOTS OF PEOPLE.

22:49.875 --> 22:51.667
IT'S STARTING.

22:51.667 --> 22:53.667
[MOVIE MUSIC PLAYING]

23:00.250 --> 23:02.708
SO WHAT'S HE LIKE?

23:02.708 --> 23:06.875
THIS GUY YOU'RE SO AFRAID
TO ADMIT YOU'RE GAGA OVER.

23:06.875 --> 23:08.083
I AM NOT GAGA.

23:08.083 --> 23:09.500
EXCUSE ME?

23:09.500 --> 23:12.208
HOW WELL DO WE
KNOW EACH OTHER NOW?

23:12.208 --> 23:13.417
NOT AT ALL.

23:13.417 --> 23:16.834
UH, WHICH IS EXACTLY WHY
YOU SHOULD TELL ME THE TRUTH.

23:16.834 --> 23:19.166
MY ADVICE WILL BE
TOTALLY NEUTRAL.

23:21.166 --> 23:23.500
HE'S...

23:23.500 --> 23:24.708
A COOK.

23:24.708 --> 23:27.250
WELL, HE BAKES BREAD,
ACTUALLY.

23:27.250 --> 23:32.083
AND HE JUST SO HAPPENS
TO BE MY ROOMMATE'S
EX-BOYFRIEND.

23:32.083 --> 23:33.750
MMM. MINOR LEAGUE.

23:33.750 --> 23:36.458
WHAT OTHER EXCUSES
ARE YOU GONNA THROW AT ME?

23:36.458 --> 23:38.041
COME ON,
I'VE HEARD THEM ALL.

23:38.041 --> 23:39.667
YOU'VE NEVER
HEARD THIS ONE.

23:39.667 --> 23:40.792
TRY ME.

23:41.417 --> 23:43.959
DO YOU BELIEVE IN GOD?

23:43.959 --> 23:46.375
THAT DEPENDS.

23:46.375 --> 23:49.125
IT CAN'T DEPEND.
EITHER YOU DO
OR YOU DON'T.

23:49.125 --> 23:52.708
IT DEPENDS WHETHER
YOU'RE GONNA RUIN
A PERFECTLY DECENT EVENING

23:52.708 --> 23:54.917
BY TRYING TO CONVERT
ME TO SOMETHING.

23:56.959 --> 23:59.166
MY ROOMMATE...

23:59.166 --> 24:02.083
SHE GOT MUGGED
THE OTHER NIGHT.

24:02.500 --> 24:04.917
I'M SORRY.

24:04.917 --> 24:06.333
ANYWAY, SHE...

24:06.333 --> 24:08.250
LEFT ME
THIS MESSAGE,

24:08.250 --> 24:10.875
WHICH, OF COURSE,
I DIDN'T GET UNTIL
THE NEXT MORNING,

24:10.875 --> 24:13.250
BECAUSE I WAS
HAVING SEX WITH
HER EX-BOYFRIEND.

24:13.250 --> 24:16.166
AND ON IT,
SHE SAID THAT
SHE WAS OK

24:16.166 --> 24:17.708
AND THAT SHE WAS
SPENDING THE NIGHT
WITH A FRIEND

24:17.708 --> 24:18.333
AND NOT TO WORRY.

24:18.333 --> 24:20.291
BUT YOU DID.
YEAH.

24:20.291 --> 24:21.500
I COULD TELL
BY HER VOICE

24:21.500 --> 24:24.041
THAT SOMETHING WAS
REALLY, REALLY WRONG.

24:24.041 --> 24:25.166
SO I...

24:25.166 --> 24:29.417
MADE THIS DEAL WITH GOD.

24:31.125 --> 24:33.458
I SAID "GOD,
PLEASE LET JOEY BE OK.

24:33.458 --> 24:35.458
"LIKE, REALLY
AND TRULY OK,

24:35.458 --> 24:37.834
"AND I WILL
WALK THE PATH
OF MORAL RIGHTEOUSNESS.

24:37.834 --> 24:39.125
I WILL DO EVERYTHING
RIGHT FOR A CHANGE."

24:39.125 --> 24:43.375
SO NO MORE TRYING TO PICK UP
GUYS IN ROCK AND ROLL BANDS?

24:43.375 --> 24:44.333
[LAUGHS]

24:44.333 --> 24:45.875
WELL, GOD DOESN'T
WANT ME TO BE A NUN.

24:45.875 --> 24:48.959
OH, HE JUST WANTS
YOU TO GIVE UP THIS
ONE PARTICULAR GUY.

24:48.959 --> 24:50.792
YES.

24:50.792 --> 24:52.667
I MEAN, HE MUST,
YOU KNOW?

24:52.667 --> 24:54.959
IT'S GOT TO BE, LIKE,
SOME KIND OF SIGN.

24:54.959 --> 24:58.959
OTHERWISE,
THIS WHOLE THING WITH
PACEY IS JUST TOO...

24:58.959 --> 25:01.208
TOO WHAT?

25:01.208 --> 25:03.708
EASY.

25:05.667 --> 25:08.041
MAYBE THAT'S YOUR SIGN.

25:12.708 --> 25:16.166
OK, I DIDN'T SAY FUNNY,
I SAID CLEVER.

25:16.166 --> 25:18.166
OH, AND CLEVER IS BAD?

25:18.166 --> 25:18.917
CLEVER IS DISTANCING.

25:18.917 --> 25:21.333
CLEVER PUTS UP
THIS WALL

25:21.333 --> 25:23.000
BETWEEN YOU
AND THE AUDIENCE.

25:23.000 --> 25:24.667
SO YOU CAN'T
TRUST CLEVER.

25:24.667 --> 25:27.208
I SEE. SO IN GENERAL,
YOU TRUST PASSION.

25:27.208 --> 25:30.083
HAS PASSION ALWAYS
STEERED YOU RIGHT IN LIFE?

25:30.083 --> 25:32.208
WELL, I MEAN,

25:32.208 --> 25:35.667
NO, NOT IN LIFE, BUT...

25:35.667 --> 25:36.792
BUT IN ART.

25:36.792 --> 25:40.792
YEAH,
BUT ART IS SUPPOSED
TO BE PASSIONATE.

25:40.792 --> 25:42.458
ART IS SUPPOSED
TO MAKE YOU FEEL--

25:42.458 --> 25:43.333
NO, NO.

25:43.333 --> 25:45.458
LIFE IS SUPPOSED
TO MAKE YOU FEEL.

25:45.458 --> 25:48.750
ART IS SUPPOSED
TO MAKE YOU FEEL GOOD.

25:48.750 --> 25:49.834
IS THAT ALL THAT ART
IS SUPPOSED TO DO?

25:49.834 --> 25:54.708
NO, BUT IF YOU NEED IT
TO DO MORE, THEN...

25:54.708 --> 25:57.000
MAYBE THERE'S SOMETHING
WRONG WITH YOUR LIFE.

25:59.750 --> 26:02.417
ARE YOU SAYING THAT
THERE IS SOMETHING
WRONG WITH MY LIFE?

26:02.417 --> 26:03.875
I--I DON'T KNOW.

26:03.875 --> 26:05.542
I DON'T REALLY
KNOW YOU THAT WELL.

26:06.625 --> 26:09.542
FOR EXAMPLE,
DO YOU HAVE A BOYFRIEND?

26:10.375 --> 26:13.917
YOU ALREADY
ASKED ME THAT.

26:13.917 --> 26:15.542
YOU DIDN'T ANSWER.

26:16.333 --> 26:19.417
WELL, WHY DO YOU
KEEP ASKING?

26:19.417 --> 26:21.291
BECAUSE I'M INTERESTED.

26:21.291 --> 26:24.750
[SIGHS]
IN WHAT?

26:24.750 --> 26:26.750
IN YOU.

26:28.500 --> 26:31.291
OH, GOSH, NO...

26:31.291 --> 26:33.875
I DO HAVE A BOYFRIEND.

26:33.875 --> 26:34.917
YOU'RE MAKING IT UP.

26:34.917 --> 26:36.208
JUST NOW.
YOU'RE MAKING THAT UP.

26:36.208 --> 26:37.417
NO. NO, REALLY.
UM...

26:37.417 --> 26:38.583
I DO HAVE
A BOYFRIEND,

26:38.583 --> 26:43.375
AND HE'S
A REALLY NICE GUY.

26:43.375 --> 26:46.250
AND I...

26:46.250 --> 26:48.083
WOULDN'T
IN A HUNDRED
MILLION YEARS,

26:48.083 --> 26:49.583
DO ANYTHING
TO HURT HIM.

26:49.583 --> 26:50.583
SO...

26:50.583 --> 26:50.959
I GOT IT.

26:50.959 --> 26:53.542
OK.

26:53.542 --> 26:55.625
GOOD.

26:55.625 --> 26:57.250
THE CARBONARA'S
NOT A CREAM SAUCE?

26:57.250 --> 26:59.291
NO. IT'S RAW EGG
YOLK, ACTUALLY.

26:59.291 --> 27:00.250
SO WHILE IT
COULD KILL YOU,

27:00.250 --> 27:01.208
WHO WANTS
TO LIVE IN A WORLD

27:01.208 --> 27:02.208
WHERE FOOD ISN'T
AN ADVENTURE, RIGHT?

27:02.208 --> 27:03.959
[LAUGHS]

27:03.959 --> 27:04.417
NOW.

27:04.417 --> 27:06.625
RIGHT, UM...

27:06.625 --> 27:09.125
JEFF, THERE'S SOMETHING
I GOTTA TELL YA.

27:09.125 --> 27:11.125
I'M NOT, UH...

27:11.959 --> 27:16.708
THE THING IS,
I'M NOT TOTALLY...

27:16.708 --> 27:18.250
TOTALLY, UH...

27:18.250 --> 27:19.959
AVAILABLE?

27:19.959 --> 27:21.834
YOU'RE NOT AVAILABLE.
THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE
TRYING TO SAY.

27:21.834 --> 27:23.291
YES. THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT I'M TRYING TO SAY.

27:23.291 --> 27:25.250
I SORT OF SUSPECTED.

27:25.250 --> 27:28.750
YOU SEEM VERY...

27:28.750 --> 27:29.750
TOGETHER.

27:29.750 --> 27:31.291
AND WE ARE.

27:31.291 --> 27:33.000
WELL, IT WAS NICE
MEETING YOU BOTH.

27:34.041 --> 27:34.959
YOU KNOW,

27:34.959 --> 27:36.834
I DON'T USUALLY DO THIS,

27:36.834 --> 27:38.708
BUT WHAT THE HELL.

27:39.500 --> 27:40.417
[SIGHS]

27:40.417 --> 27:42.583
IF YOU GUYS EVER BREAK UP,

27:42.583 --> 27:44.750
GIVE ME A CALL SOMETIME.

27:51.792 --> 27:54.625
WHAT JUST HAPPENED
RIGHT THERE?

27:55.583 --> 27:56.708
I THINK THAT
I SHOULD BE INSULTED

27:56.708 --> 27:59.500
ON SEVERAL DIFFERENT
LEVELS ABOUT THAT.

27:59.500 --> 28:00.708
[CHUCKLES]
PACEY, YOU'RE NOT GAY.

28:00.708 --> 28:02.667
WELL, I  KNOW THAT
AND YOU  KNOW THAT,

28:02.667 --> 28:04.583
BUT HE  DOESN'T
KNOW THAT.

28:04.583 --> 28:05.667
SO FAR AS HE'S
CONCERNED,

28:05.667 --> 28:07.041
YOU'RE MY BOYFRIEND.

28:07.041 --> 28:09.083
Humphrey Bogart: I KNOW.
IT'S JUST ANOTHER PICTURE.

28:09.083 --> 28:11.125
Man: ARE YOU IN ANY
POSITION TO BE CHOOSY?

28:11.125 --> 28:12.375
YOU HAVEN'T WRITTEN A HIT
SINCE BEFORE THE WAR.

28:12.375 --> 28:14.333
AND YOUR LAST PICTURE--

28:14.333 --> 28:15.542
Bogart: SO IT STUNK.

28:15.542 --> 28:17.500
EVERYBODY MAKES FLOPS
EXCEPT YOU.

28:17.500 --> 28:19.291
YOU HAVEN'T HAD ONE
BECAUSE YOU'VE MADE
AND RE-MADE

28:19.291 --> 28:20.417
THE SAME PICTURE
FOR THE LAST 20 YEARS.

28:20.417 --> 28:22.667
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU ARE?
YOU'RE A POPCORN SALESMAN.

28:22.667 --> 28:24.041
Man: THAT'S RIGHT.
SO ARE YOU.

28:24.041 --> 28:27.291
THE ONLY DIFFERENCE
BETWEEN US IS THAT
I DON'T FIGHT IT.

28:27.291 --> 28:29.166
Bogart: ONE DAY
I'LL SURPRISE YOU

28:29.166 --> 28:30.208
AND WRITE SOMETHING GOOD.

28:30.208 --> 28:31.333
Man: ALTHEA BRUCE
WILL DO IT.

28:31.333 --> 28:32.375
Bogart: ALTHEA BRUCE--

28:32.375 --> 28:33.959
Man: ALL YOU GOTTA DO
IS FOLLOW THE BOOK...

28:33.959 --> 28:35.792
EXCUSE ME.

28:37.166 --> 28:38.333
Second Man: HIYA, KIDDIES.

28:38.333 --> 28:40.375
WHAT A PICTURE I MADE.

28:40.375 --> 28:41.959
JUST GOT BACK
FROM THE PREVIEW.

28:41.959 --> 28:43.792
PASADENA'S OUT OF ITS MIND...

29:01.708 --> 29:03.375
GREAT TITLE.

29:03.375 --> 29:05.500
I THINK I MIGHT
STEAL IT FOR SOMETHING.

29:05.500 --> 29:09.166
HOW'D YOU KNOW IT WAS ME?

29:09.166 --> 29:10.917
SAW YOU WHEN
YOU CAME IN.

29:10.917 --> 29:11.458
SHOULD I BE JEALOUS?

29:11.458 --> 29:13.333
ARE YOU JEALOUS?

29:13.333 --> 29:14.291
[EXHALES]
LIKE MEDEA.

29:15.542 --> 29:17.583
HE'S JUST A FRIEND.

29:17.583 --> 29:18.834
MINE'S NOT.
NOT WHAT?

29:18.834 --> 29:22.083
A FRIEND.
I MEAN, SHE IS, BUT,

29:22.083 --> 29:23.333
SOMETIMES WE GO OUT,

29:23.333 --> 29:24.333
AND WE HAVE
A FEW DRINKS,

29:24.333 --> 29:25.291
WE GO BACK TO MY PLACE.

29:25.291 --> 29:26.583
SHE FORGETS WHY
I'M NOT RIGHT FOR HER.

29:26.583 --> 29:27.417
WHY ARE YOU TELLING ME THIS?

29:27.417 --> 29:28.583
I'M TRYING
TO GET YOU TO HATE ME.

29:28.583 --> 29:30.667
WELL, IT'S WORKING.

29:32.583 --> 29:36.333
SO WHAT IS THE BEST ENDING
IN ALL OF LITERATURE?

29:36.333 --> 29:37.917
DON'T SAY ULYSSES.
EVERYONE SAYS ULYSSES.

29:39.708 --> 29:40.834
THAT'S EASY.

29:40.834 --> 29:43.333
SENTIMENTAL EDUCATION
BY FLAUBERT.

29:43.333 --> 29:43.875
AND WHAT HAPPENS?

29:43.875 --> 29:45.583
NOTHING, REALLY.

29:45.583 --> 29:47.250
JUST 2 OLD FRIENDS
SITTING AROUND

29:47.250 --> 29:49.417
REMEMBERING
THE BEST THING THAT
NEVER HAPPENED TO THEM.

29:49.417 --> 29:52.708
HOW DO YOU REMEMBER SOMETHING
THAT NEVER HAPPENED?

29:54.208 --> 29:55.166
FONDLY.

29:56.542 --> 29:57.792
YOU SEE,
FLAUBERT BELIEVED

29:57.792 --> 29:59.625
THAT ANTICIPATION
WAS THE PUREST FORM
OF PLEASURE...

29:59.625 --> 30:02.125
AND THE MOST RELIABLE.

30:02.125 --> 30:05.500
AND THAT WHILE
THE THINGS THAT
ACTUALLY HAPPEN TO YOU

30:05.500 --> 30:06.458
WOULD INVARIABLE
DISAPPOINT,

30:06.458 --> 30:07.417
THE THINGS THAT
NEVER HAPPENED TO YOU

30:07.417 --> 30:11.083
WOULD NEVER DIM.

30:11.083 --> 30:12.792
NEVER FADE.

30:12.792 --> 30:14.625
THEY WOULD ALWAYS BE
ENGRAVED IN YOUR HEART

30:14.625 --> 30:17.875
WITH A SORT OF
SWEET SADNESS.

30:19.500 --> 30:20.750
THAT SOUNDS...

30:21.291 --> 30:22.750
DEEP?

30:24.500 --> 30:25.917
COWARDLY.

30:27.708 --> 30:28.750
[SIGHS]

30:28.750 --> 30:31.875
WELL, UH, US ACADEMICS

30:31.875 --> 30:33.083
AREN'T
GENERALLY KNOWN FOR--

30:43.083 --> 30:44.041
COURAGE.

30:45.375 --> 30:47.834
WOW.

30:48.750 --> 30:50.500
GOD IS REALLY
PUNISHING ME HERE.

30:50.500 --> 30:51.917
FOR WHAT?

30:51.917 --> 30:53.166
I DON'T KNOW.

30:53.166 --> 30:57.250
I MUST HAVE DONE
SOMETHING TO A GIRL
WHEN I WAS 18.

30:57.250 --> 31:01.166
YOU'RE NOT TRYING
TO TEMPT ME INTO
RECONSIDERING, ARE YOU?

31:02.917 --> 31:05.875
NO.

31:05.875 --> 31:08.708
WE DON'T KNOW EACH OTHER
VERY WELL, DO WE?

31:08.708 --> 31:10.750
NO, WE DON'T.

31:10.750 --> 31:12.750
YOU HAVE THIS IMAGE OF ME,

31:12.750 --> 31:15.834
THIS NOT-ENTIRELY-TRUE
IMAGE OF ME.

31:15.834 --> 31:17.834
AS A 19th-CENTURY
HEROINE?

31:17.834 --> 31:19.333
YEAH.

31:20.208 --> 31:22.708
AND EVEN THOUGH
THAT'S NOT TRUE,

31:22.708 --> 31:26.667
I'D RATHER YOU GO ON
THINKING THAT IT IS.

31:29.458 --> 31:31.000
I THINK THAT
CAN BE ARRANGED.

31:33.875 --> 31:36.875
I SHOULD PROBABLY
GET BACK.

31:38.667 --> 31:39.041
ARE WE OK HERE?

31:41.333 --> 31:43.917
WE'RE FINE.

31:47.708 --> 31:50.333
IN 5 YEARS...

31:50.333 --> 31:51.834
YOU'RE GONNA KNOW
EVERYTHING I KNOW

31:51.834 --> 31:53.083
AND MORE.

31:53.083 --> 31:56.875
AND I WILL SEEM
LIKE THE BIGGEST DORK
YOU EVER MET.

31:59.458 --> 32:02.708
OR MAYBE I ALREADY DO.

32:22.917 --> 32:25.041
HEY.

32:26.291 --> 32:27.917
HEY.

32:27.917 --> 32:30.417
I WAS JUST ABOUT
TO COME BACK INSIDE.

32:30.417 --> 32:32.792
DON'T BOTHER.

32:32.792 --> 32:33.667
WOULD YOU CARE
TO ELABORATE

32:33.667 --> 32:34.750
ON WHAT YOU WERE
SAYING EARLIER?

32:34.750 --> 32:36.959
[SIGHS]

32:36.959 --> 32:37.792
YOU'LL MISS THE REST
OF YOUR MOVIE.

32:37.792 --> 32:39.834
[LAUGHS]
I HAVE A FEELING

32:39.834 --> 32:41.208
THIS MIGHT BE
A LITTLE MORE INTERESTING.

32:46.291 --> 32:49.166
Joey: DID YOU EVER MEET
SOMEONE WHO SAW YOU...

32:49.166 --> 32:51.291
I MEAN, REALLY SAW YOU...

32:51.291 --> 32:54.125
BUT SOMEHOW,
ONLY SAW THE BEST?

32:54.125 --> 32:55.000
Dawson:
YOU MEAN BESIDES YOU?

32:55.000 --> 32:57.166
NOT THAT. I MEAN,
SOMEONE OLDER.

32:57.166 --> 33:01.125
SOMEONE WHO SAW
EVERYTHING YOU COULD BE.

33:01.125 --> 33:03.625
IF ONLY...

33:03.625 --> 33:04.667
IF ONLY WHAT?

33:04.667 --> 33:08.083
IF ONLY YOU WEREN'T YOU.

33:08.083 --> 33:09.041
[CHUCKLES]

33:09.041 --> 33:10.792
WELL, AFTER TONIGHT,

33:10.792 --> 33:12.250
I KINDA THINK
YOU MIGHT NOT BE.

33:13.625 --> 33:15.834
YOU KISSED
YOUR PROFESSOR.

33:15.834 --> 33:16.959
[LAUGHS]

33:16.959 --> 33:18.834
YOU KISSED THE GUY
WHO GIVES YOU GRADES.

33:18.834 --> 33:19.917
IS THIS CONSTRUCTIVE?

33:19.917 --> 33:21.959
SORRY.

33:21.959 --> 33:25.166
SO THE WORST PART IS,
IS THAT

33:25.166 --> 33:26.625
THAT NIGHT WHEN YOU
CALLED FROM THE MOVIE SET...

33:26.625 --> 33:28.750
YEAH?

33:28.750 --> 33:30.959
I WAS THERE
AT HIS HOUSE. ALONE.

33:30.959 --> 33:34.000
AND I WENT THERE
SAYING TO MYSELF

33:34.000 --> 33:35.959
THAT I WAS JUST GOING
TO STRAIGHTEN EVERYTHING OUT.

33:35.959 --> 33:36.875
MM-HMM.

33:36.875 --> 33:38.125
BUT REALLY, YOU WERE
GOING OVER THERE

33:38.125 --> 33:39.667
TO MAKE THINGS
MORE COMPLICATED.

33:39.667 --> 33:41.959
I DON'T THINK
THE ANSWER TO THAT

33:41.959 --> 33:43.250
WOULD SOUND VERY JOEY-LIKE.

33:43.250 --> 33:44.333
I THINK WE'RE GONNA
HAVE TO COME UP

33:44.333 --> 33:46.542
WITH A NEW DEFINITION
FOR THE TERM JOEY-LIKE.

33:48.500 --> 33:49.500
ANYWAY, SO YOU CALLED,

33:49.500 --> 33:52.208
I LEFT, AND I OBVIOUSLY
DIDN'T GO BACK,

33:52.208 --> 33:53.417
WHICH IS PROBABLY
A GOOD THING, BECAUSE...

33:53.417 --> 33:58.333
I WOULD HAVE MADE
A GIGANTIC FOOL OF MYSELF.

33:59.792 --> 34:00.875
DON'T SAY THAT.

34:00.875 --> 34:02.375
YOU TOOK A RISK.

34:02.375 --> 34:04.917
YOU LIVED.
YOU EXPERIENCED
SOMETHING, RIGHT?

34:04.917 --> 34:06.792
I GUESS.
BUT NOW I'LL NEVER KNOW.

34:06.792 --> 34:09.291
NEVER KNOW WHAT?

34:10.333 --> 34:11.000
WHAT I WOULD HAVE DONE...

34:11.000 --> 34:13.833
AT THAT MOMENT OF TRUTH.

34:13.833 --> 34:15.375
YOU KNOW, WOULD I HAVE
CHICKENED OUT,

34:15.375 --> 34:19.125
